.TH "phylink_stop" 9 "phylink_stop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phylink_stop \- stop a phylink instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" phylink_stop
.BI "(struct phylink *pl "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pl" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct phylink\fP returned from \fBphylink_create\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Stop the phylink instance specified by \fIpl\fP. This should be called from the
network device driver's \fIstruct net_device_ops\fP \fBndo_stop\fP method.  The
network device's carrier state should not be changed prior to calling this
function.
